inID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D354515%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sunita%20and%20Suhas%20Ramegowda%20run%20'The%20Good%20Gift'%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20is%20bringing%20back%20the%20age-old%20practice%20of%20making%20rag%20dolls%20based%20around%20craft-making.%20While%20doing%20so%2C%20they%20have%20prevented%208%2C000%20kg%20of%20textile%20waste%20from%20entering%20the%20landfills%20and%20empowered%20at%20least%20200%20tribal%20women%20in%20the%20Nilgiris.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20quit%20teaching%20to%20become%20a%20luxury-travel%20advisor.%20Since%20making%20the%20transition%2C%20I've%20learned%20a%20lot%20and%20grown%20professionally.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kaylee%20Stith%20sits%20at%20a%20cafe%20and%20smiles%20into%20the%20camera%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6675bd2a65f501a881813413%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKaylee%20Stith%20is%20a%20former%20teacher%20who%20decided%20last%20spring%20to%20pursue%20luxury-travel%20advising.%3Cp%3EDanielle%20James%20Studios%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKaylee%20Stith%20left%20teaching%20to%20join%20The%20Travel%20Mechanic%20as%20a%20travel%20agent%20last%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStith%20leveraged%20her%20organizational%20skills%20from%20teaching%20for%20her%20new%20role%20in%20travel%20advising.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20article%20is%20part%20of%C2%A0%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ftrends-to-bet-your-career-on%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrends%20to%20Bet%20Your%20Career%20On%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20series%20about%20trending%20professional%20opportunities.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKaylee%20Stith%20is%20a%20travel%20agent%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthetravelmechanic.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Travel%20Mechanic%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20luxury-travel%20agency%20in%20North%20Carolina.%20This%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Stith%2C%20who%20left%20her%20full-time%20teaching%20job%20to%20become%20a%20luxury-travel%20agent%20last%20year.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20started%20travel%20advising%2C%20I%20worked%20as%20a%20middle-school%20special-education%20teacher%20in%20North%20Carolina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stumbled%20upon%20the%20travel-agent%20industry.%20I%20was%20following%20someone%20on%20Instagram%20who%20recently%20started%20her%20own%20Disney-specific%20travel%20agency.%20I%20love%20Disney%2C%20and%20when%20she%20announced%20that%20she%20was%20hiring%20an%20agent%2C%20I%20thought%20that%20would%20be%20a%20fun%20part-time%20job.%20I%20applied%20and%20made%20it%20through%20the%20first%20round.%20I%20didn't%20get%20hired%2C%20but%20I%20couldn't%20stop%20thinking%20about%20becoming%20a%20travel%20advisor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%2C%20I%20started%20exploring%20on%20my%20own.%20I%20listened%20to%20podcasts%20about%20the%20industry%20and%20learned%20more%20from%20the%20American%20Society%20of%20Travel%20Advisors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20I%20was%20listening%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.travelweekly.com%2FPodcasts%2FTrade-Secrets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrade%20Secrets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20travel-agent%20podcast%2C%20when%20they%20interviewed%20Lauren%20Doyle%2C%20the%20president%20and%20owner%20of%20The%20Travel%20Mechanic%2C%20an%20agency%20based%20where%20I%20live%20in%20Raleigh%2C%20North%20Carolina.%20I%20filled%20out%20the%20form%20for%20prospective%20agents%20and%20interviewed%2C%20and%20I%20was%20offered%20a%20position%20on%20the%20team.%20I%20signed%20a%20contract%20on%20April%201%2C%202023%2C%20and%20left%20my%20full-time%20teaching%20role%20in%20June%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f4e1c8a1-9e2e-4644-ae95-4d0cd0664d54%5C%22%3ESkills%20I%20transferred%20from%20my%20teaching%20career%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20my%20skills%20transferred%20from%20teaching%2C%20like%20being%20organized%20and%20helping%20people.%20Because%20I%20came%20from%20a%20special-education%20setting%2C%20I%20was%20often%20the%20liaison%20between%20students%20and%20their%20teachers.%20Being%20a%20travel%20advisor%20is%20similar%20because%20you're%20connecting%20with%20your%20clients%20and%20interfacing%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20transition%20was%20also%20a%20challenge%2C%20because%20I%20forgot%20what%20it%20feels%20like%20not%20to%20know%20what%20you're%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20is%20a%20commercial%20airline%20pilot%2C%20and%20I've%20been%20traveling%20my%20whole%20life%20and%20planning%20my%20own%20trips%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20I%20assumed%20I'd%20naturally%20slide%20into%20this%20role%20and%20automatically%20know%20how%20to%20do%20everything.%20But%20there's%20a%20lot%20to%20learn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20very%20practical%20things%20I%20had%20to%20learn%2C%20like%20how%20to%20use%20the%20customer-relationship-management%20system%20we%20put%20client%20information%20into%2C%20how%20to%20take%20payments%2C%20and%20how%20to%20make%20sure%20clients%20are%20signing%20off%20on%20the%20right%20terms%20and%20conditions%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lot%20of%20that%20was%20new%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ea5f422f-4120-49b8-bf69-f49f284c4144%5C%22%3EHow%20I%20make%20money%20as%20an%20advisor%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20offer%20a%20complimentary%20consultation%20and%20discuss%20options%20with%20the%20client%20to%20ensure%20we're%20both%20a%20good%20fit.%20Then%20I%20charge%20a%20flat-rate%20planning%20fee.%20Some%20agents%20have%20a%20base%20amount%2C%20and%20depending%20on%20how%20complicated%20the%20trip%20is%20or%20how%20many%20people%20are%20going%2C%20they%20might%20charge%20more.%20Once%20the%20client%20pays%20the%20fee%2C%20I%20put%20their%20itinerary%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20make%20a%20commission%20on%20things%20like%20hotels%20and%20tour%20packages.%20Some%20suppliers%20will%20pay%20a%20decent%20commission%3B%20if%20you%20work%20on%20the%20higher%20end%2C%20you%20make%20a%20bigger%20commission.%20Commissions%20are%20usually%20paid%20out%20after%20the%20client%20has%20finished%20the%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20I%20work%20with%20The%20Travel%20Mechanic%2C%20I%20get%20some%20leads%2C%20but%20I%20have%20to%20find%20most%20of%20them%20on%20my%20own.%20So%20a%20big%20part%20of%20this%20job%20is%20telling%20everyone%20I'm%20a%20travel%20agent.%20I'll%20mention%20it%20in%20conversations%20with%20people%20I%20meet%20because%20it's%20travel%2C%20it's%20fun%2C%20and%20people%20enjoy%20talking%20about%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20clients%20have%20so%20far%20been%20in%20my%20circles.%20I've%20worked%20with%20several%20people%20from%20my%20church%2C%20friend%20groups%2C%20and%20family.%20Sometimes%20it's%20good%20to%20start%20with%20the%20people%20near%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f967ea8f-a5b6-412c-8069-bb2d74187834%5C%22%3EHave%20a%20niche%20when%20you're%20starting%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20good%20to%20have%20a%20niche%20to%20present%20yourself%20as%20an%20expert%20in%20when%20starting%20out.%20My%20niches%20are%20Hawaii%20and%20the%20UK%20because%20they're%20what%20I%20know%20and%20love.%20My%20family%20loves%20Hawaii%2C%20and%20I've%20visited%20regularly%20since%20I%20was%209.%20I've%20also%20been%20to%20England%20many%20times.%20I%20studied%20abroad%20in%20college%20and%20lived%20in%20Bath%20for%20four%20months%20as%20a%20student.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20locations%20are%20similar%20in%20some%20ways%20because%20they're%20higher-ticket%20bucket-list%20destinations.%20They're%20also%20great%20destinations%20for%20first-time%20travelers%20who%20want%20to%20adventure%20out%20on%20a%20bigger%20trip%20but%20go%20somewhere%20that%20feels%20familiar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHawaii%20is%20still%20far%20away%2C%20but%20the%20driving%20and%20currency%20are%20familiar.%20Though%20England%20is%20also%20pretty%20far%20away%2C%20the%20language%20and%20culture%20are%20not%20that%20different%20from%20the%20US.%20Those%20are%20my%20two%20favorite%20destinations%2C%20and%20I%20do%20some%20Disney%20trips%20on%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2260dd113c-293b-4a7b-b179-15cd9f7e97cc%5C%22%3EAdvice%20for%20prospective%20travel%20agents%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20think%20this%20job%20is%20fun%20and%20relatively%20easy%20to%20get%20into.%20You%20don't%20need%20specific%20training%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20get%20going.%20It's%20a%20marathon%2C%20not%20a%20sprint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20get%20into%20travel%20advising%2C%20I%20recommend%20starting%20part%20time%20or%20having%20another%20source%20of%20income%20before%20you%20get%20established%20and%20move%20to%20full%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20research.%20This%20will%20help%20you%20see%20if%20you're%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20the%20industry%20and%20find%20an%20agency%20you%20feel%20aligned%20with%20that%20will%20support%20you.%20If%20you're%20unsure%20where%20to%20start%2C%20visit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhostagencyreviews.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHost%20Agency%20Reviews%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20research%20agencies%20near%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20possible%20to%20go%20at%20it%20alone%2C%20starting%20with%20an%20agency%20is%20easier.%20Your%20commissions%20with%20an%20agency%20may%20be%20a%20bit%20lower%2C%20but%20an%20agency%20will%20offer%20advice%20and%20assist%20you%20when%20you're%20starting%20out%20with%20leads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22395bfe01-aaea-4a2c-adde-95d39c94b0e5%5C%22%3ELessons%20I've%20learned%20so%20far%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20attended