hose.%20If%20you%20are%20at%20a%20VP%20or%20director%20level%2C%20you%20can%20either%20be%20really%20good%20at%20your%20job%20or%20a%20pleasure%20to%20work%20with.%20You%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20both%2C%20and%20sometimes%20people%20are%20still%20neither.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20at%20the%20bottom%2C%20where%20the%20%26quot%3Bactual%20work%20is%20being%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Morris%20said%2C%20don't%20tend%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-happy-jobs-never-want-be-managers-promotions-randstad-workmonitor-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emove%20up%20the%20ladder%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20they%20keep%20doing%20it%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20get%20out%20of%20that%20cycle%2C%20but%20I%20believe%20in%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20curse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22tiktok%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20cite%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40jacquelameo%2Fvideo%2F7356278433367821610%5C%22%20data-video-id%3D%5C%227356278433367821610%5C%22%20data-embed-from%3D%5C%22oembed%5C%22%3E%20%3Csection%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40jacquelameo%3Frefer%3Dembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%40jacquelameo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%40jacquelameo%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cp%3Ebut%20if%20I%20take%20a%20week%20off%20everything%20falls%20apart%3F%20it%20ain%E2%80%99t%20adding%20up%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2Fmusic%2Foriginal-sound-7356278554184796971%3Frefer%3Dembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%E2%99%AC%20original%20sound%20-%20jacqueline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%99%AC%20original%20sound%20-%20jacqueline%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fsection%3E%20%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5633fc0-f94f-4670-a985-5067a5be1d72%5C%22%3EA%20glass%20ceiling%20for%20the%20agreeable%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20sounds%20cynical%2C%20but%20Morris%20might%20be%20onto%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Bramson%2C%20who%20offers%20leadership%20training%20programs%20as%20CEO%20of%20The%20Paul%20Bramson%20Companies%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20competent%2C%20likable%20employees%20%26quot%3Boften%20face%20a%20glass%20ceiling%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20promotions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBramson%20said%20that%20when%20people%20have%20an%20underlying%20need%20to%20be%20liked%2C%20executive%20leaders%20can%20see%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bweakness%26quot%3B%20or%20an%20inability%20to%20make%20tough%20decisions%20or%20have%20difficult%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lack%20of%20firmness%20or%20assertiveness%20can%20be%20problematic%2C%20as%20it%20might%20seem%20like%20the%20individual%20isn't%20taking%20people%20and%20decisions%20in%20hand%20effectively%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20a%20generalisation.%20A%20company's%20corporate%20culture%20and%20leadership%20style%20will%20impact%20which%20personality%20traits%20are%20considered%20during%20promotions.%20A%20person's%20specific%20role%20and%20skill%20set%20also%20affect%20how%20much%20their%20personality%20changes%20their%20career%20trajectory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20on%20what%20traits%20workplaces%20favor%20is%20mixed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.myscience.uk%2Fnews%2F2018%2Fwhy_it_doesn_t_pay_to_be_just_nice_you_also_need_to_be_intelligent-2018-bristol%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%202018%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Universities%20of%20Bristol%2C%20Minnesota%2C%20and%20Heidelberg%20found%20that%20being%20nice%20and%20conscientious%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Btransitory%20and%20small%26quot%3B%20impact%20on%20someone's%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.truity.com%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FPersonalityType-CareerAchievementStudy.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETruity%20Psychometrics%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20company%20that%20designs%20personality%20and%20career%20tests%2C%20logical%2C%20analytical%20people%20tend%20to%20manage%20larger%20teams%20than%20those%20who%20are%20considered%20agreeable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisagreeable%20men%20in%20the%20workplace%20also%20have%20an%20edge%20and%20are%20paid%20more%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.nd.edu%2Fnews%2Fmen-earn-a-premium-for-being-disagreeable-in-the-workplace-women-dont-says-new-research%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%202011%20research%20conducted%20by%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20University%20of%20Notre%20Dame%2C%20Cornell%20University%2C%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Western%20Ontario.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%202020%20study%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.2005088117%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20in%20Proceedings%20of%20the%20National%20Academy%20of%20Sciences%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20selfish%2C%20combative%2C%20and%20manipulative%20people%20are%20no%20more%20likely%20to%20get%20ahead%20at%20work%20than%20their%20good-hearted%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Cameron%20Anderson%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20organizational%20behavior%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%20at%20Berkeley%20who%20conducted%20the%20study%2C%20dominance%20and%20kindness%20are%20both%20associated%20with%20rising%20up%20the%20ranks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdo-jerks-get-ahead-toxic-work-promotions-salary-power-career-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20previously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20assertiveness%20of%20being%20a%20jerk%20can%20help%2C%20but%20Anderson's%20study%20suggests%20their%20lack%20of%20generosity%20holds%20them%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a66cd07e-1aa9-4537-940a-dcbea9c9bd99%5C%22%3EPerformance%20punishment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20say%20that%20in%20some%20organizations%2C%20high%20performers%20get%20overloaded%20with%20more%20work%20but%20aren't%20necessarily%20rewarded%20or%20promoted%2C%20which%20is%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bperformance%20punishment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMary%20McConner%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Inclusive%20Excellence%20Consulting%2C%20told%20BI%20this%20is%20when%20high%20performers%20get%20overloaded%20with%20work%20because%20they%20are%20reliable.%20People%20with%20an%20agreeable%20nature%20can%20find%20themselves%20in%20the%20same%20boat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20performance%20punishment%20often%20leads%20to%20burnout%20and%20resentment%20because%20their%20good%20work%20isn't%20rewarded%20with%20advancement%2C%20but%20with%20more%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20McConner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20cooperative%20and%20reliable%20employees%20are%20strong%20contenders%20for%20promotions%2C%20they%20may%20be%20overlooked%20if%20they%20are%20perceived%20as%20less%20assertive%20or%20they%20are%20taken%20for%20granted%2C%20she%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMary%20Barnes%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20business%20consultancy%20Evolve%20Your%20Performance%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20in%20organizations%20with%20toxic%20cultures%2C%20%26quot%3Bskewed%20values%20and%20misaligned%20metrics%20prevail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20certain%20environments%2C%20overconfident%20people%20with%20dark%20triad%20traits%20can%20easily%20climb%20the%20ranks%20and%20perpetuate%20a%20destructive%20cycle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20such%20environments%2C%20pleasant%20and%20competent%20employees%20often%20get%20sidelined%2C%26quot%3B%20Barnes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20healthier%20companies%20with%20better%20cultures%2C%20leaders%20can%20prioritize%20people%20who%20are%20emotionless%20and%20rational%2C%20Barnes%20added.%20But%20it's%20soft%20skills%20that%20are%20actually%20vital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BManaging%20down%20requires%20empathy%20and%20empowerment%2C%20treating%20people%20like%20whole%20humans%20instead%20of%20cogs%20in%20a%20corporate%20wheel%2C%26quot%3B%20Barnes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20viewers%20of%20Morris'%20video%20likened%20her%20observation%20to%20%26quot%3BThe%20Peter%20Principle%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-performing-managers-set-harsher-targets-for-workers-study-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20management%20concept%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Canadian%20educationist%20Lawrence%20J.%20Peter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20explains%20how%20people%20can%20be%20promoted%20based%20on%20their%20previous%20success%20rather%20than%20their%20suitability%20for%20a%20new%20role%2C%20finding%20themselves%20in%20positions%20they%20don't%20yet%20have%20the%20skills%20for%2C%20and%20thus%20reach%20%26quot%3Ba%20level%20of%20respective%20incompetence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarnes%20said%20that%20people%20promoted%20to%20leadership%20positions%20may%20stop%20being%20so%20kind%20and%20competent%20if%20they%20struggle%20with%20this%20conundrum%20and%20start%20overcompensating%20for%20their%20imposter%20syndrome%20and%20micromanaging%20without%20empathy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFew%20master%20this%20balance%2C%20and%20those%20who%20don't%20are%20destined%20to%20become%20mediocre%20leaders%20at%20best%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22826bf78c-7ce7-42ff-a342-784b9a0da9aa%5C%22%3EBeing%20nice%20but%20ballsy%20can%20pay%20off%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELuke%20Blaney%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20the%20recruitment%20agency%20ARx%2C%20told%20BI%20there%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20truth%20in%20the%20whole%20'nice%20guys%20finish%20last'%20saying.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEspecially%20if%20people%20aren't%20prepared%20to%20even%20ask%20for%20what%20they%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlaney%20said%20it's%20all%20in%20the%20delivery%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-promoted-at-work-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easking%20for%20a%20raise%20or%20a%20promotion%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20being%20ballsy%20enough%20to%20ask%20is%20the%20same%20as%20not%20being%20pleasant%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarolina%20Caro%2C%20a%20leadership%20coach%20and%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20Conscious%20Leadership%20Partners%2C%20thinks%20times%20are%20changing%2C%20however.%20She%20told%20BI%20that%20she%20thinks%20the%20notion%20of%20being%20a%20tough%20leader%20is%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20outdated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%2C%20businesses%20are%20now%20interested%20in%20people%20who%20can%20handle%20tough%20situations%20%26quot%3Btactfully%20and%20with%20compassion%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOrganizations%20are%20recognizing%20the%20need%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20development%20of%20their%20leaders%20so%20that%20they%20can%20be%20the%20type%20of%20leader%20that%20people%20want%20to%20work%20for%20and%20foster%20engagement%2C%26quot%3B%20Caro%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20goal%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20all%20the%20organizations%20are%20there%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20have%20%26quot%3Bremnants%20of%20archaic%20leadership%20models%20where%20the%20more%20aggressive%20you%20are%20as%20a%20leader%2C%20the%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Caro%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20this%20type%20of%20leadership%20is%20generally%20seen%20as%20ineffective%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BParticularly%20in%20today's%20landscape%20with%20a%20multigenerational%20workforce%20that%20expects%20something%20completely%20different%2C%20or%20they%20simply%20leave.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsome-truth-nice-guys-finishing-last-work-perso