artAsset%20analyzed%20the%20most%20recently%20available%20US%20Census%20data%20for%2037%20of%20the%20largest%20US%20cities%20to%20determine%20where%20birth%20rates%20and%20family%20sizes%20are%20the%20highest%20and%20lowest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20looked%20at%20the%20number%20of%20women%20aged%2015%20to%2050%20who%20had%20a%20baby%20in%20the%2012%20months%20between%202021%20and%202022%2C%20comparing%20this%20with%20the%20total%20number%20of%20women%20in%20that%20age%20bracket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndianapolis%20topped%20the%20list%2C%20with%20Seattle%20ranked%20lowest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20suggested%20that%206.5%25%20of%20Indianapolis%20women%20aged%2015%20to%2050%20had%20a%20child%20in%202022%2C%20leading%20to%2014%2C482%20births.%20In%20Seattle%2C%20it%20was%20just%202.6%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20found%20that%20birth%20rates%20in%20major%20cities%20were%20lower%20than%20the%20national%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBirth%20rates%20are%20a%20crucial%20indicator%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcity-metro-population-growth-from-2022-to-2023-florida-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epopulation%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20happening%20in%20the%20US%20is%20we%20have%20more%20people%20dying%20than%20birth%20in%20some%20of%20these%20metropolitan%20areas%2C%26quot%3B%20Emilio%20A.%20Parrado%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania's%20Population%20Studies%20Center%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParrado%20emphasized%20that%20high%20birth%20rates%20in%20Indianapolis%20could%20have%20significant%20policy%20and%20urban%20planning%20implications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20include%20preventing%20school%20closures%2C%20increasing%20demand%20for%20childcare%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bproducing%20children%20that%20are%20going%20to%20maintain%20Indianapolis%20if%20they%20don't%20leave%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParrado%20said%20there%20was%20insufficient%20data%20in%20the%20analysis%20to%20directly%20attribute%20the%20higher%20birth%20rates%20to%20a%20particular%20cause%2C%20but%20factors%20such%20as%20domestic%20and%20international%20migration%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20high%20proportion%20of%20women%20of%20prime%20childbearing%20age%2C%20likely%20contribute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParrado%20also%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20study's%20limitation%20in%20not%20controlling%20for%20age%20makes%20it%20challenging%20to%20distinguish%20between%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthrowing-money-schemes-wont-solve-global-fertility-crisis-demography-experts-2024-6%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBy%25202100%252C%252097%2525%2520of%2520countries%2Creverse%2520population%2520decline%252C%2520they%2520said.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efertility%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20population's%20age%20composition%2C%20and%20that%20a%20more%20precise%20measure%20would%20be%20the%20total%20fertility%20rate%2C%20which%20estimates%20the%20number%20of%20children%20a%20woman%20is%20expected%20to%20have%20over%20her%20lifetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20most%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.in.gov%2Fhealth%2Freports%2Fnatality%2F2017%2Ftbl31_t.htm%26source%3Dgmail-imap%26ust%3D1720021046000000%26usg%3DAOvVaw3z7xKjx1fYI_KQo1Ar5u-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndiana%20natality%20report%2C%20from%202017%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Marion%20County%2C%20which%20includes%20Indianapolis%2C%20had%20a%20total%20fertility%20rate%20of%201.933%2C%20higher%20than%20the%20overall%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraph.co.uk%2Fus%2Fnews%2F2024%2F04%2F27%2Fus-birth-rate-falls-to-record-low-amid-global-decline%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20rate%20of%201.62.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20demographers%20and%20governments%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasia-countries-worry-fertility-rate-affect-armies-few-soldiers-experts-202